cs.CE, cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.SC, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper evaluates the performance of a domain specific language (DSL) for finite differences on high-performance computing (HPC) processors, which is relevant to computational science and engineering.
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper specifically focuses on evaluating the performance of Arm ThunderX2 processors, which falls under the hardware architecture category.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses the performance of Devito on HPC processors, which is related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing.
- cs.SC (Scientific Computing): The paper evaluates the performance of Devito on seismic computational kernels, which is relevant to scientific computing.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the performance of a specific DSL on a specific type of processor, which can be considered as a system and control problem.
